  "response": "Several artists have released songs titled \"You.\" Here are a few notable examples:\n\n1. **The Pixies**  \n   - *Album:* *Surfer Rosa* (1988)  \n   - A track from their influential alternative rock album.\n\n2. **Jesse Powell**  \n   - *Album:* *Jessie* (1998)  \n   - An R&B song known for its smooth vocals and romantic lyrics.\n\n3. **Robin Thicke**  \n   - *Single:* \"You\" (2003)  \n   - An upbeat R&B track showcasing Thicke\u2019s vocal range.\n\n4. **Taylor Swift**  \n   - *Album:* *Folklore* (2020)  \n   - A soft, introspective song from her critically acclaimed album.\n\n5. **TENSETFIVE**  \n   - An electronic track titled \"You,\" known within the electronic music scene.\n\n6. **Marvin Gaye**  \n   - *Single:* \"You\" (1981)  \n   - A soulful ballad from the legendary Motown artist.\n\n7. **Billie Eilish**  \n   - *Single:* \"You\" (2022)  \n   - A contemporary pop song with her signature style.\n\n8. **SZA**  \n   - *Album:* *SOS* (2022)  \n   - A track blending R&B and contemporary sounds.\n\nThese are just a few examples, and there are many other artists across various genres who have songs titled \"You.\" If you have a specific genre or artist in mind, feel free to provide more details!",
